      "amount": "2 tbsp"
    },
    {
      "name": "white chocolate",
      "amount": "50g",
      "notes": "low-fat"
    },
    {
      "name": "olive oil",
      "amount": "1 tbsp"
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "Rinse the soaked navy beans and set aside.",
    "Heat the olive oil in a large pot over medium heat.",
    "Add the diced onion, carrot, celery, and minced garlic; cook until softened.",
    "Stir in the smoked paprika and black pepper and cook for 1 minute.",
    "Add the beans and vegetable broth, bring to a boil, then reduce heat.",
    "Simmer uncovered for 45 minutes, stirring occasionally, until the beans are tender.",
    "Stir in the chopped parsley and white chocolate; let the chocolate melt completely.",
    "Serve the chowder hot, optionally topping with toasted breadcrumbs if desired."
